Reasoning: The paper discusses network infrastructure and fault-tolerance, which are topics typically covered in the Computer Networks and Communications (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses targeted attacks and adversarial faults, which are relevant to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The discussion of centralized and decentralized network structures suggests the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) may also be relevant. The paper also discusses trust transitivity and redundancy, which are topics relevant to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Information Theory (cs.IT), respectively.
